  "prompt": "What is the temperature on the planet Mercury at the demarcation point between light and dark?",
  "response": "The temperature on Mercury at the demarcation point between light and dark, also known as the terminator, can vary widely due to the planet's lack of a significant atmosphere to distribute heat evenly. During the day, temperatures can soar to around 430\u00b0C (800\u00b0F), while at night, they can plunge to approximately -180\u00b0C (-290\u00b0F). At the terminator, the temperature would be somewhere between these extremes, gradually transitioning from the blistering heat of the day side to the frigid cold of the night side. However, an exact temperature at the terminator can be difficult to specify due to the rapid change in temperature over a relatively short distance.",
